SAC COUNTY WIND, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Sac County Wind, LLC ("Sac County Wind") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Sac County Wind generating facility ("Sac County Wind Facility").
Sac County Wind is a wind turbine generating facility located in Odebolt, Iowa. The Sac County Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by MidAmerican Energy Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Sac County Wind's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Sac County Wind Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Sac County Wind's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Sac County Wind shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $260,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $21,666.67.
